sense.name: kill by squeezing one's throat
sense.examples: He tied her jeans around her neck and strangulated her. If it is too tight, Wilbur could strangulate. Such cords were used to strangulate horses.

sense.name: become constricted
sense.examples: It permits the state to strangulate the right to choose abortion. I might garble, strangulate my words. His story quickly turned dreary and strangulated. The positive valence would be strangulated. I felt so strangulated talking that I turned to writing songs.
